# CREATIVE_BELIEFS.md — Addy's Visual Intelligence

> **Loaded by:** `playbooks/CREATIVES.md` only — NOT at morning brief startup.
> **Purpose:** Retain what works and what flops specifically for this brand's creative production.
> Zero trial-and-error repetition across sessions.
>
> **How it works:**
> - Addy reads this at the START of every CREATIVES.md session (before Step 1)
> - At the END of a creative session, Addy asks: did anything change a standing belief?
>   - If yes → revise in place, update confidence + date
>   - If no → write nothing
> - Log of what was tried/failed goes in `review/YYYY-MM-DD_creatives.md`
>   This file only holds compressed beliefs — not a session transcript
>
> **Confidence levels:** CONFIRMED / LIKELY / HYPOTHESIS / SUPERSEDED
>
> **Format:**
> ```
> ### [CR-ID] Short belief statement
> Confidence: LEVEL | Last updated: YYYY-MM-DD | Evidence: [source]
> Detail: one or two sentences
> ```

---

## Brand Constraints

### [CR-01] Logo requires a white or light background — transparent/dark backgrounds bleed
Confidence: HYPOTHESIS | Last updated: 2026-07-03 | Evidence: Standard brand guideline — not yet tested in Higgsfield
Detail: AnrakLegal logo has dark elements that disappear on dark overlays. Always place on white or very light background. Validate on first Higgsfield run and update confidence.

### [CR-02] Product UI screenshots need breathing room — tight crops lose context
Confidence: HYPOTHESIS | Last updated: 2026-07-03 | Evidence: UI design inference — not yet tested
Detail: The product interface (chat, feed, case tools) needs surrounding whitespace to read clearly at ad thumbnail scale. Full-bleed UI crops likely render as noise. Test on first creative session.

